OL,3,CStalking and drink spiking could
OL,4,Cbecome offences under new abuse law
OL,6,FDrink spiking, stalking and non-fatal
OL,7,Fstrangulation could be made specific
OL,8,Foffences in Guernsey under a new law.
OL,10,FA register may also be created for
OL,11,Fconvicted domestic abusers to reduce
OL,12,Fthe risk of reoffending.
OL,14,FThe island's Home Affairs Committee is
OL,15,Fconsidering adding a second phase of
OL,16,Fproposals to the Domestic Abuse Law
OL,17,F2024 which is now in the final stages
OL,18,Fof consultation.
